This paper deals with the analysis of algorithms for approximate inference in large Gaussian latent variable models. This topic is closely related to machine learning and statistical inference, which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as it covers the broad area of machine learning, including Bayesian inference. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely category as it deals with the analysis of algorithms and their convergence properties. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as it covers the area of intelligent systems, which includes machine learning and statistical inference. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as it deals with the analysis of networks, which can be used to model dependencies between latent variables. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as it covers the area of neural networks, which can be used to model complex dependencies between variables.
